The paper discusses the use of deep learning methods for computer vision tasks in microscopy-based point of care diagnostics. This suggests that the paper is likely to belong to the computer vision (cs.CV) sub-category. Additionally, the use of deep learning methods implies that the paper may also belong to the artificial intelligence (cs.AI) and machine learning (cs.LG) sub-categories. The evaluation of the performance of deep convolutional neural networks suggests that the paper may also belong to the data structures (cs.DS) sub-category. Finally, the use of microscopy-based point of care diagnostics suggests that the paper may also belong to the information retrieval (cs.IR) sub-category.
